**Instance Types**
- **t2.micro** is given for free tier account with 1GB storage and EBS volume.
**1.General Purpose:**
**T2 Instances:** Low-cost, burstable performance for general-purpose workloads.
**Example:** Development, testing, small web applications.
**T3 Instances:** Burstable performance with a baseline level of CPU performance.
**Example:** Microservices, small web apps, development environments.
**2.Compute Optimized:**
**C5 Instances:** Compute-optimized instances with high CPU performance.
**Example:** Batch processing, high-performance computing (HPC), data analytics.
**3.Memory Optimized:**
**R5 Instances:** Memory-optimized instances with high RAM-to-CPU ratio.
**Example:** In-memory databases, big data analytics, data caching.
**X1 Instances:** Memory-optimized instances with massive RAM capacity.
**Example:** In-memory databases, SAP HANA, in-memory analytics.
**4.Storage Optimized:**
**I3 Instances:** High-performance instances with local NVMe SSD storage optimized for I/O-intensive applications.
**Example:** NoSQL databases, data warehousing, real-time analytics.
**D3 Instances:**  Storage-optimized instances with high disk throughput.
**Example:** Big data processing, data warehousing, data lakes.
**H1 Instances:** Dense storage-optimized instances for large-scale data processing.
**Example:** Big data analytics, distributed file systems.
**5.Specialized Compute:**
**P3 Instances:** Accelerated computing with powerful GPUs for machine learning, deep learning, and HPC.
**Example:** Machine learning training, scientific simulations.
**G4 Instances:**  GPU instances optimized for graphics-intensive applications and machine learning.
**Example:** Video encoding, 3D rendering, AI inferencing.
**F1 Instances:** FPGA (Field-Programmable Gate Array) instances for customizable hardware acceleration.
**Example:** Custom hardware acceleration for specialized workloads.
**Z1d Instances:** High-frequency CPU instances with fast single-threaded performance.
**Example:** Gaming servers, electronic design automation.
