**Elastic Block Storage (EBS)**
**——————————————**
- EBS are the storage volumes that can be attached to Amazon EC2 instance.
- It can attach to only one instance at a time.
- File systems and databases can be installed on these storage.
- It protects data from external disk failures within the availability zone.
- To attach to multiple instances at a time you can use Elastic File Storage.
- **Types:**
- 1. General Purpose SSD (gp2)
- 2. Provisioned IOPS SSD (io1)
- 3. Throughout Optimized HDD (st1)
- 4. Cold HDD (sc1)
